How to avoid typescript from checking a particular line?
To disable type-checking for a specific line in TypeScript, you can use the `@ts-ignore` directive.

Here is an example of how to use it:

```typescript
function sayHi(name: string): void {
  @ts-ignore 
  // The following line will not be checked by TypeScript
  name = "pepe";
}
```

This directive tells TypeScript to ignore type checking for the next statement. Just replace `// ...` with your non-TypeScript code and it won't be checked.

Do note that this is considered bad practice, because it might cause errors in your application. It's better to define types correctly rather than using `@ts-ignore`.
